      SamlIdpUrlBuilder Application.newSamlIdpUrlBuilder()
      Creates a new SamlIdpUrlBuilder that allows you to build a URL you can use to redirect your application users to a SAML authentication site (Identity Provider or IdP) for performing common user identity functionality.

      SamlIdpUrlBuilder SamlIdpUrlBuilder.setAccountStoreHref(String accountStoreHref)
      Sets the ash property used by the SAML Identity Provider to complete a SAML authentication workflow.
      SamlIdpUrlBuilder SamlIdpUrlBuilder.setCallbackUri(String callbackUri)
      Sets the location where the user will be sent when returning from the SAML Identity Provider.
      SamlIdpUrlBuilder SamlIdpUrlBuilder.setOrganizationNameKey(String organizationNameKey)
      Ensures the SAML Identity Provider is customized for the Organization with the specified organizationNameKey.
      SamlIdpUrlBuilder SamlIdpUrlBuilder.setPath(String path)
      Sets the initial path in the SAML Identity Provider where the user should be sent.
      SamlIdpUrlBuilder SamlIdpUrlBuilder.setSpToken(String spToken)
      Sets the sp_token property used by the SAML Identity Provider to complete an account password reset workflow.
      SamlIdpUrlBuilder SamlIdpUrlBuilder.setState(String state)
      Sets application-specific state that should be retained and made available to your callbackUri when the user returns from the SAML Identity Provider.
